----------------------------------------------------------------
 PnZigbeeSwitch reports class_name "Switch" instead of
 "Zigbee Switch"
----------------------------------------------------------------

(1) pn-zigbee-switch.c:405 pins node_class->class_name = "Zigbee
    Switch", but pn_node_get_class_name() on an instance returns
    "Switch". The PnSwitch base seeds a *per-instance* class-name
    label (the legacy override path), and the instance value shadows
    the subclass's class-level value. The other nodes derive from
    PnNode directly and are unaffected (they report their correct
    class_name). Likely surfaced by commit 5fd9ad9, which dropped
    the deprecated pn_node_set_class_name() calls from node init.
    1.1 Decide whether the palette/inspector should show "Zigbee
        Switch" (it should). If so, re-assert the per-instance label
        in pn_zigbee_switch_init (the supported setter), or have the
        host stop seeding an instance-level override from PnSwitch.
        Caught by tests/test-zigbee-switch.c (which currently does
        not assert class_name for this reason).
    1.2 Update (2026-05-29): the host getter was already fixed for
        this -- pipnode commit 97acd76 made pn_node_get_class_name()
        fall back to the class-level PnNodeClass.class_name when there
        is no per-instance override (lib/pn-node.c:889-898), and
        deprecated pn_node_set_class_name() for plugin _init() use.
        That alone does NOT fix us, though: PnSwitch's own
        pn_switch_init still seeds a per-instance "Switch"
        (lib/pn-switch.c:462) -- 97acd76 cleaned up pn_mqtt_init but
        left pn-switch.c -- so the getter finds that non-empty
        per-instance value and never reaches the new class-level
        fallback. Decided fix: drop the pn_node_set_class_name (node,
        "Switch") line at pn-switch.c:462 in pipnode (mirroring the
        pn_mqtt_init cleanup); then PnZigbeeSwitch inherits "Zigbee
        Switch" for free. To be done in pipnode later; once landed,
        enable the class_name assertion in tests/test-zigbee-switch.c.


----------------------------------------------------------------
 Code-review findings (2026-05-29)
----------------------------------------------------------------

Found by a multi-agent review of the full source. No
memory-safety or registration bugs were found; ownership of
JsonNode / GString / PnMessage is correct throughout. The items
below are behavioral / contract issues.

(2) success flag: switch's configured vs unconfigured paths
    disagree (minor).
    data.success=FALSE is the section-12 downstream failure signal
    -- i.e. "did the node do its job". These nodes only build and
    emit a message (a downstream PnMqttSink does any actual
    publishing; nothing touches hardware), so no property
    combination can stop them emitting and success = TRUE is correct
    by design. The configured paths (pn-zigbee-switch.c:156,
    pn-zigbee-relay-command.c:190, pn-zigbee-relay-status.c:210) get
    this right. The lone wrinkle: the base PnSwitch builder
    overloads success to carry the latch state (success = on,
    ../pipnode/.../pn-switch.c:124). That leaks into the Zigbee
    switch *only* on the unconfigured fallback path
    (pn-zigbee-switch.c:133-134), so within one node success means
    "always true" when configured but "is-on" when not.
    2.1 Optionally make the unconfigured fallback also stamp
        success = TRUE for self-consistency. Low priority -- the
        unconfigured case is a misconfiguration the warning visual
        already flags, and success is correct on the path that
        matters.

(3) PnZigbeeSource: malformed/empty bridge/devices is dropped and
    leaves a stale cache.
    src/pn-zigbee-source.c:731-737, :592-596 -- a garbage or
    momentarily-[] inventory publish is swallowed (default
    filter_bridge_devices=TRUE), the device cache is not refreshed,
    and nothing is logged; the node then runs on stale device info
    invisibly. (Deeper than the section-12 logging for :590.)
    3.1 Log a warning on the not-an-array / empty case, and consider
        keeping the previous cache when the new array is empty.

(4) Boolean Z2M state is silently dropped (switch & relay nodes).
    src/pn-zigbee-relay-command.c:116-122,
    src/pn-zigbee-relay-status.c:146, src/pn-zigbee-switch.c:220 --
    value/state readers accept only string / int64 / double, so Z2M
    endpoints that express "state": true as a JSON boolean are
    ignored. Consistent across the three, so a gap rather than a
    divergence.
    4.1 Optionally accept G_TYPE_BOOLEAN for state / value.

(5) PnZigbeeRelayStatus leaves the live device state topic on its
    emitted message.
    src/pn-zigbee-relay-status.c:204-218 -- never calls
    pn_message_set_topic, unlike relay-command which rewrites it
    (:166-168). Wiring relay-status to an MQTT Sink that republishes
    on the inbound topic would echo onto the device's state topic.
    Latent foot-gun.
    5.1 Clear the topic on the emitted message, or document why it's
        left intact.

----------------------------------------------------------------
 Devices dialog: Connect/Disconnect toggle review findings
 (2026-05-31)
----------------------------------------------------------------

Found by a multi-agent review of src/pn-zigbee-gui.c after the
"make Connect a Connect/Disconnect toggle" commit. No memory-safety
bugs (no leak / double-free / UAF; the owned combo active-text is
freed, msg_handler is disconnected before unref, the combo "changed"
guard correctly no-ops during programmatic populate). The items
below are behavioral / contract issues the new disconnect path made
reachable, plus reuse cleanups.

(6) Behavioral issues from the toggle.
    6.1 Open join (pairing) window is left dangling on Disconnect /
        broker-change. zb_reset_to_disconnected -> zb_drop_source
        clears ctx->sink but never calls zb_join_finish, so the modal
        countdown stays up, zb_join_tick -> zb_join_publish silently
        no-ops (sink == NULL), the renewals stop AND the final
        permit_join {value:false} close is never published -- the
        coordinator can keep accepting devices for up to ~254 s after
        the UI says "disconnected" (security-relevant, treat as the
        priority fix). Fix: call zb_join_finish (ctx, TRUE) in the
        teardown path BEFORE g_clear_object (&ctx->sink) so the close
        actually goes out; zb_join_finish is idempotent and ctx-safe.
    6.2 A connected-but-silent broker cannot be disconnected via the
        button. ctx->connected is set TRUE only on the first publish
        (zb_on_message, count==1), but zb_on_apply_clicked branches on
        it: if the broker connects while Z2M never publishes (Z2M
        down / empty topic tree), the button stays "Connect" and each
        press silently re-runs zb_start_source (reconnect) instead of
        tearing down -- the live session is undroppable from the
        button. Fix: drive the button label/toggle off session
        existence (ctx->source != NULL), keeping ctx->connected only
        for the green Status bullet. zb_on_broker_changed already keys
        on ctx->source != NULL; align the button with it.
    6.3 Unguarded json_node_get_string at zb_build_action_row (~:1751)
        on values[0] with no JSON_NODE_HOLDS_VALUE / string-type check
        -- a non-string future payload logs a g_critical. Every other
        consumer routes through the type-safe zb_json_to_display.
        Harmless today (Z2M action values are always strings). Fix:
        guard the type or reuse zb_json_to_display.
    6.4 Reuse / simplification cleanups (no behavior change):
        6.4.1 8 near-identical "if (ctx->sink == NULL) { set_status
              ("Connect to a broker before <verb>."); return; }" guards
              -> one zb_require_sink (ctx, "writing") helper.
        6.4.2 The ref_sink/destroy/unref "discard unparented widget"
              triple is open-coded at 5 sites that could route through
              the existing zb_discard_grid (rename to zb_discard_widget).
        6.4.3 The dim "unit suffix" label block is duplicated verbatim
              in zb_build_expose_row and zb_add_int_control.
        6.4.4 Minor: grid row/col spacing 8/12 restated ~8x; status
              colors #2ecc71 / #9e9e9e inline despite the file otherwise
              #define-ing its constants.
        6.4.5 Stale comment (~:3948) claims a "nested main loop in
              zb_on_join_clicked" that no longer exists (the join flow
              was rewritten to be non-nested).
